 ## [Unreleased]
 
+### Phase 13a — Helm base chart for the reference deployment (issue #171)
+
+The first Phase 13 chunk: a Helm chart at [`reference/helm/eden/`](reference/helm/eden/) that deploys the EDEN reference services the Compose stack runs (task-store-server, orchestrator, ideator/executor/evaluator hosts, web-ui, Forgejo, Postgres; plus an opt-in control plane) on any conforming Kubernetes cluster (1.27+). The chart is **parallel** to Compose, not a replacement — both are first-class v0 substrates. The **default** is the single-experiment path (one orchestrator drives one experiment directly; no control plane), mirroring the Compose default stack that `compose-smoke` validates. See [`docs/plans/eden-phase-13a-helm-base-chart.md`](docs/plans/eden-phase-13a-helm-base-chart.md) for the plan and [`docs/deployment/helm.md`](docs/deployment/helm.md) for the operator guide.
+
+**Post-#128 opaque-id identity model.** The chart and [`setup-experiment-helm.sh`](reference/scripts/setup-experiment-helm.sh) implement the [#128](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/128) identity model, mirroring the canonical Compose `setup-experiment.sh`: the experiment id is an opaque, system-minted `exp_*` (the event model rejects any id not matching `^exp_[0-9a-hjkmnp-tv-z]{26}$`, so the script mints one when `--experiment-id` is omitted), and every per-service worker id is a server-minted `wkr_*`. The script brings the task-store-server up, then `POST {"name": ...}`s to mint the reserved `admins`/`orchestrators` groups and one worker per service (orchestrator, web-ui, ideator/executor/evaluator hosts, plus the `operator` admin actor), capturing each minted `worker_id` + one-time `registration_token`. It hands each worker_id + token to the chart as `identity.<svc>.*` values; the chart passes the worker_id as `--worker-id` and renders a per-service Secret carrying the token, which an `initContainer` installs at `/var/lib/eden/credentials/<worker_id>.token` so the pod's startup credential bootstrap verifies it via `/whoami` (no admin reissue). The minted ids + tokens are stored in the release values, so re-running the script reuses them rather than minting duplicates.
+
+**Workload-kind split (Decision 3).** StatefulSets for services that hold a per-replica local git clone (orchestrator, executor-host, evaluator-host, web-ui) plus the stateful stores (Postgres, Forgejo); Deployments for the stateless services (task-store-server, ideator-host, and — in lease mode — control-plane). StatefulSet `volumeClaimTemplates` mint one PVC per replica. Unlike the pre-port draft, the `--worker-id` is the setup-minted opaque `wkr_*` (NOT the `POD_NAME`), which is the post-#128 requirement.
+
+**Three-phase bootstrap (two render gates).** `experiment.baseCommitSha` gates the **store tier** (the task-store-server records the seed commit at first experiment-row creation); `identity.<svc>.workerId` gates each **identity-consuming service** (under #128 the pods cannot start before their minted worker_id exists). So [`setup-experiment-helm.sh`](reference/scripts/setup-experiment-helm.sh): (1) `helm upgrade --install` with the SHA empty → infra tier (Postgres, Forgejo); (2) provision the Forgejo `eden` user + seed the bare repo via a one-shot out-of-tree Job ([`bootstrap/repo-init-job.yaml.tmpl`](reference/helm/eden/bootstrap/repo-init-job.yaml.tmpl), `kubectl apply`-ed per-experiment so its lifecycle is per-experiment not per-release — the AGENTS.md multi-tenant-lifecycle pitfall), then `helm upgrade --set experiment.baseCommitSha=<sha>` → task-store-server; (3) mint the groups + per-service workers, then `helm upgrade` with the `identity.*` values → app tier (orchestrator, worker hosts, web-ui). The orchestrator self-joins the `orchestrators` group at startup under the admin token.
+
+**Lease-driven HA is opt-in and deferred behind [#281](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/281).** `orchestrator.leaseMode.enabled` (default `false`) selects between the single-experiment default and a lease-driven HA mode where the control-plane Deployment renders, the orchestrator + web-ui receive `EDEN_CONTROL_PLANE_URL`, and the script registers the experiment with the control plane. Multi-replica HA (orchestrators contending for one lease) requires reconciling the #128 per-replica opaque-id minting with #147's lease-mode orchestrator self-registration; that reconciliation is **deferred and unvalidated** behind [#281](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/281). Only the default single-experiment path is exercised by `helm-smoke`; `replicas.orchestrator` defaults to 1. Re-enable lease mode once #281 lands.
+
+**Bundled orchestrator code change (Decision 9).** Kubernetes Deployments/StatefulSets only support `restartPolicy: Always`, so the orchestrator's quiescence-exit (exit 0 when no work remains) would CrashLoopBackOff. The orchestrator CLI/loop accept `--max-quiescent-iterations 0` as a "never exit on quiescence; run until SIGTERM" sentinel ([`cli.py`](reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/cli.py) `_quiescent_iterations` accepts 0; `1` stays rejected — [`loop.py`](reference/services/orchestrator/src/eden_orchestrator/loop.py) skips the quiescence-exit branch when 0). The chart defaults `config.maxQuiescentIterations: 0`; Compose keeps its quiescence-exit lifecycle. New unit tests in [`test_loop_unit.py`](reference/services/orchestrator/tests/test_loop_unit.py) cover the 100-zero-progress-iteration never-exit path and the validator's accept-0 / reject-1 contract.
+
+**Image is the operator's responsibility (Decision 7).** The chart pulls a published image; `image.repository` + `image.tag` are required and enforced by [`values.schema.json`](reference/helm/eden/values.schema.json) (`minLength: 1`) so `helm install` fails loud at template time rather than at pod-pull time with `ErrImagePull`. The existing `reference/compose/Dockerfile` stays the single canonical image build.
+
+**Secrets + auth posture.** A single chart-managed `<release>-secrets` Secret (dev) or `secrets.existingSecret` (prod: Sealed Secrets / External Secrets / Vault), plus the per-service identity Secrets carrying the minted worker tokens. The Forgejo HTTP-Basic + git-credential-helper posture mirrors Compose byte-for-byte via a ConfigMap-mounted helper script that reads `FORGEJO_REMOTE_PASSWORD` from the pod env; 13e replaces it with per-branch ACLs + native PR review.
+
+**CI.** A fast [`helm-lint`](.github/workflows/ci.yml) job (lint + render the full single-experiment stack + render the lease-mode stack + schema fail-closed check, runs on every push) and a heavier [`helm-smoke`](.github/workflows/ci.yml) job (kind cluster + image build/load + `setup-experiment-helm.sh` against the single-experiment default + the same end-state assertions as `compose-smoke`: ≥3 `variant.integrated`, ≥9 `task.completed`, ≥3 ideation-task `task.completed`). Both are gated on a new `helm` changes-filter bucket. Per the newly-added-smoke-job convention they are not yet required by branch protection — [#286](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/286) tracks the bump after ~2 weeks clean on `main`. The local equivalent is [`reference/helm/eden/ci-smoke.sh`](reference/helm/eden/ci-smoke.sh).
+
+**Scope (13a).** Base chart + `--mode scripted` worker hosts (Decision 10) + embedded Postgres/Forgejo StatefulSets (stopgaps replaced in 13c/13e — embedding chosen over upstream subchart dependencies per plan §3.8). The artifact store is a web-ui-owned `ReadWriteOnce` PVC; the task-store-server's artifact-serving route is unwired in 13a.
+
+**Deferrals (each filed as a tracking issue at the moment of deferral).** Lease-driven HA — reconciling #128 opaque-id minting with #147's lease-mode orchestrator self-registration — → [#281](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/281). A `helm-upgrade-smoke` CI job (plan §6.3) → [#284](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/284). Cross-service artifact serving on Kubernetes (needs a `ReadWriteMany` or external blob backend) → [#285](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/285). The `helm-lint`/`helm-smoke` required-status bump → [#286](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/286). Kubernetes-native `--mode subprocess` + DooD worker hosts (Decision 10; 13a ships only `--mode scripted`) → [#291](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/291).
+
+**Subsequent Phase 13 substrate work** is pre-planned roadmap scope, tracked in [`docs/roadmap.md`](docs/roadmap.md) §"Phase 13 — Kubernetes reference deployment": GPU executor as a k8s Job (13b), managed external Postgres (13c), S3/GCS blob backend (13d), and Forgejo auth + per-branch ACLs + native PR review (13e). These are separate planned phases, not gaps left by 13a.
+
 ### Automatic checkpointing — cadence + on-terminate (issue #131)
 
 Makes the Phase 12b portable-checkpoint wire surface ([#152](https://github.com/ealt/eden/issues/152)) *happen automatically* so the operator's "I can accept interruptions / teardown / redeployment / imperfect checkpoints" posture is viable **without operator action**. A pure **consumer** of 12b: adds nothing to the checkpoint format and nothing normative to the protocol. The one `spec/`-tree edit is the `experiment-config.schema.json` `auto_checkpoint` block — an implementation-defined config knob like `max_quiescent_iterations`, kept in lockstep with the Pydantic model by the `schema-parity` job — not a protocol-prose or wire authority-table change.
